title: Understanding 'Existing Reports'
text: Before starting a new project, reviewing previous documented work can provide valuable insights and data that avoid redundancy and allow you to build upon past learnings.

title: What Are 'Existing Reports'?
text: Existing reports refer to previously completed projects or studies related to your current research area, offering a starting point by providing established data trends, methodologies, or conclusions.

title: Identifying Sources of 'Existing Reports'
text: You can find existing reports in databases, digital archives, company records, online libraries, or academic journals that have documented findings, results, and recommendations.
